[resource]
script = ExtResource("1_mbnyv")
reagent_id = "NaOH"
title = "Sodium hydroxide"
body = "[b]Basic facts[/b]
[table=2]
[cell]Formula:[/cell][cell]NaOH[/cell]
[cell]Molar mass:[/cell][cell]40 g/mol[/cell]
[cell]State at room temperature:[/cell][cell]Solid (white)[/cell]
[cell]Type:[/cell][cell]Strong base (alkali)[/cell]
[/table]
[b]Formation reactions[/b]
2Na + 2H₂O → 2NaOH + H₂  
Na₂O + H₂O → 2NaOH
[b]Important properties[/b]
• Highly soluble in water.
• Forms a strong alkaline solution.
• Corrosive — can damage skin and materials.
• Reacts with acids to form salt and water.
[b]Where it is used[/b]
• Making soap and detergents.
• Cleaning products (drain cleaners).
• Production of paper and textiles.
• Used in many chemical reactions.
[b]Safety[/b]
Very corrosive — can cause burns on skin and eyes.
Must be handled with protective equipment."
